author: pburba
msg: Fix some C-test failures with BDB backend.
(create_repos_and_wc): BDB 4.4+ allows only a single environment handle
to be open per process, so create the test repository with a subpool then
destroy the subpool so the repository's underlying filesystem is closed.
This avoids any attempt to open a second environment handle within the
same process when we later checkout a WC from the test repos.  This
solves the failures I reported here
